<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-12-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-01-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="89" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d89">
                                        <head>
                                            <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                                        </head>
                                        <p>No official <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> record
                                            of this meeting has been found in Department of State
                                            files and no list of participants is available.
                                            Secretary of Defense <persName corresp="#p_LOVETTRA1">Lovett</persName> presumably headed the United
                                            States Delegation at this meeting. The telegraphic
                                            report printed <hi rend="italic">infra</hi> is the only
                                            record of the meeting available to the editors.</p>
                                    </div>
                                    </body></text></TEI>